              <foreground color="-16711423"/>
              <inheritsPopupMenu value="false"/>
              <selectedTextColor color="-16711423"/>
              <text value="General:&#10;- HexOust is a two-player game on a base-7 hegonal board&#10;- Each player has a colored stone assigned (red or blue)&#10;&#10;Goal:&#10;- Completely clearing the board from all your opponent's stones by capturing them&#10;- Draws are NOT possible in this game&#10;&#10;Stones placement:&#10;- Non-capturing placement (NPC):&#10;&#9;1. Forms no connections (adjacencies) with any stones&#10;&#9;2. Forms one or more connections only with enemy stones&#10;&#9;3. Does NOT form any connections with stones of its own color&#10;- Capturing placement (CP):&#10;&#9;It happens when a player places a stone which forms one or more connections with their own stone (creates a new, larger group). A player can only make such a placement if the new group will have one or more connections with the opponent’s groups upon its creation AND if all opponent’s groups are smallerc than the new group. Upon making such a placement, all opponent’s groups with connections with the placed stone are removed from the board&#10;- Invalid placement:&#10;&#9; Sometimes a placement migth not be valid, so the interface is going to warn you that you cannot place your stone in that cell&#10;- Winning placement:&#10;&#9;If a player places a stone that eliminates all the opponent's stones, then they win the match&#10;&#10;&#10;Turns:&#10;- Usually a player concludes their turn by making a non-capturing placement&#10;- After capturing the opponent's stones, a player will continue to add their own stones until the they make a non-capturing placement. Therefore, a player can make multiple placements per turn and can potentially clean up all the opponent’s groups&#10;&#10;How to play this game:&#10;- The board starts out empty&#10;- The red player plays first &#10;- A player place a stone on the board, in a valid cell:&#10;&#9;- If the player made an NCP then it will become the opponent player’s turn&#10;&#9;- If the player made an CP then it will stay their turn until a NPC is made or no more valid placements are available&#10;&#9;- The first player that makes a winning placement wins the game " noi18n="true"/>
